dataIdInfo.idAbs:
The Scottish Wildlife Trust manages over 15,000 hectares of Scotland for the benefit of both people and wildlife. Our work is varied, from protecting ospreys to peatland restoration and bringing back Atlantic woodlands on a landscape scale. The majority of work on our reserves is carried out by our dedicated Reserve Project Groups which are made up of committed volunteers who lend their time to help with hands on conservation work.

Further information about our reserves and the work that we do can be found via our website: https://scottishwildlifetrust.org.uk/our-work/our-wildlife-reserves/.

Our reserve boundaries are available to download in shapefile (OSGB) format here.

Any copies made of these data, in any form, must carry the copyright text: © Scottish Wildlife Trust ([year]).

These data are provided under CC-BY licence and may be freely copied and re-used, provided that such uses are fully attributed.

Scottish Wildlife Trust reserve boundaries are updated continuously. It is the user's responsibility to ensure the most up to date version is downloaded.
